  "term": "thm:product-rule",
  "kind": "Theorem",
  "title": "Product Rule",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $A \\subseteq \\mathbb{R}$, let $f, g : A \\to \\mathbb{R}$, and let $c \\in A$ be a limit point of $A$. If $f$ and $g$ are differentiable at $c$, then $fg$ is differentiable at $c$, and\n\\[\n(fg)'(c) = f'(c)g(c) + f(c)g'(c).\n\\]",
